{
  "id": "phekb-sepsis-comprehensive",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "sepsis",
  "name": "Sepsis - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying sepsis patients via Condition + MedicationRequest + Observation. Path C captures empirical antibiotic use without sepsis dx. Path D captures cryptic shock (elevated lactate without sepsis dx).",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete sepsis patient population for an antimicrobial stewardship initiative. Some patients have a coded sepsis or septic shock diagnosis. Others were started on broad-spectrum antibiotics empirically without a formal sepsis diagnosis. Some have only an elevated lactate without yet getting a sepsis diagnosis. Run multiple FHIR queries \u2014 diagnosis, antibiotics, and lactate \u2014 and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all sepsis patients.",
    "broad": "Find all sepsis patients \u2014 by diagnosis (sepsis, bacterial sepsis, septic shock), broad-spectrum antibiotics (vancomycin, ceftriaxone), or elevated lactate (>2 mmol/L). Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "Run three queries. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|91302008,http://snomed.info/sct|10001005,http://snomed.info/sct|76571007 \u2014 sepsis dx variants. (2) MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|11124,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|2193 \u2014 vanc+ceftriaxone. (3) Observation?code=http://loinc.org|2524-7&value-quantity=gt2||mmol/L \u2014 elevated lactate. Union the patient IDs."
  },
